text: Muhammed Ali (/mɔːˈlɑːnə mʊˈhɑːməd ɑːˈliː/; Arabic: محمد علي; 1874 – 13 October 1951) was an Indian writer and leading figure of the Lahore Ahmadiyya Movement for the Propagation of Islam. ==References== Category:20th-century Indian writers Category:Indian journalists Category:20th-century Indian poets Category:Indian activists Category:Indian Muslims Category:1878 births Category:1931 deaths Category:Presidents of the Indian National Congress
